## 3. Day in the Life: {{ agent_role_title }} (~80 min)

### 3a. Starting the Day: CS Workspace

| | |
|---|---|
| **What to Say** | "When a {{ agent_role_title }} logs in, this is their home. No separate apps to open. Everything starts here. I can see: my assigned cases with color-coded tier levels, SLA timers, priority cases, and my workload across all channels -- email, phone, and chat -- in one view." |
| **Differentiation** | Unified workspace replaces multiple application windows. SLA timers are live. Tier-level pills show customer importance at a glance. |
| **Show** | My Active Cases view with Tier Level column, priority indicators, SLA countdown, case origin icons. |

---

### 3b. Email Case Creation & Copilot

| | |
|---|---|
| **What to Say** | "Let's walk through what happens when a customer emails the team. {{ email_scenario_intro }} Here, the system identified the customer, created the case, linked the email thread, populated the issue details, AND applied your routing rules. Zero manual steps. And Copilot summarizes the full picture in seconds." |
| **Differentiation** | Auto-case creation + auto-customer matching + auto-routing vs. manual triage. Copilot summarization eliminates reading entire email chains. |
| **Show** | Inbound email, auto-created case, Copilot summary, suggested response draft. |

